# kNearme Content Maintenance and Freshness Framework

This document outlines the systematic approach to maintaining content freshness, accuracy, and relevance across all service categories and content levels in the kNearme platform.

## Content Lifecycle Management

Every piece of content on kNearme should follow this defined lifecycle:

```
┌────────────┐      ┌────────────┐      ┌─────────────┐      ┌────────────┐
│  Creation  │ ──→  │ Publication │ ──→  │ Maintenance │ ──→  │ Archiving  │
└────────────┘      └────────────┘      └─────────────┘      └────────────┘
       ↑                                       │
       └───────────────────────────────────────┘
                 (Refresh/Update)
```

## Freshness Indicators

All content should have these metadata elements tracked:

- `created_date`: Original publication date
- `last_updated`: Most recent substantive update
- `next_review`: Scheduled date for next review
- `review_frequency`: How often this content should be reviewed
- `freshness_score`: Algorithm-based freshness rating (0-100)
- `content_owner`: Team/person responsible for maintenance

