## Trigger-Based Updates

Establish clear triggers that automatically flag content for review:

### Traffic-Based Triggers
- 20%+ drop in organic traffic over 30 days
- 30%+ increase in bounce rate
- Significant decline in average time on page
- Drop in conversion rates

### Search-Based Triggers
- Decline in keyword rankings (>5 positions)
- Emergence of new related search terms
- Changes in search intent signals
- Featured snippet opportunities/losses

### External Triggers
- Industry regulation changes
- Building code updates
- Material/cost significant changes
- New techniques or technologies
- Competitor content improvements

## Content Freshness Implementation

### Code-Level Implementation

```javascript
// Freshness calculation example (simplified)
function calculateFreshnessScore(content) {
  const now = new Date();
  const lastUpdated = new Date(content.lastUpdated);
  const daysSinceUpdate = (now - lastUpdated) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24);
  
  // Base score diminishes over time
  let freshnessScore = 100 - Math.min(daysSinceUpdate / 3, 50);
  
  // Traffic trend factor
  if (content.trafficTrend < -0.15) {
    freshnessScore -= 20;
  }
  
  // Search position factor
  if (content.keywordPositionChange < -3) {
    freshnessScore -= 15;
  }
  
  // Content completeness factor
  freshnessScore += content.completenessScore * 0.2;
  
  return Math.max(0, Math.min(100, freshnessScore));
}

// Update schedule generator
function generateUpdateSchedule(contents) {
  return contents
    .map(content => ({
      ...content,
      freshnessScore: calculateFreshnessScore(content),
      priority: determinePriority(content)
    }))
    .sort((a, b) => a.priority - b.priority)
    .map((content, index) => ({
      ...content,
      scheduledUpdate: calculateUpdateDate(content, index)
    }));
}
```

